reviews.review_text:
Eye(s) opener Obviously not the most memorable shows when it comes down to it, but of the hundred or so shows I attended during the early 80's and 90's, that night in the Orlando Arena sticks out in my memory. It was during the early Bruce Hornsy days with the band and his piano sounded so good.

I recall being hassled by some drunk ass redneck during intermission who "didn't care what my ticket said cause I was sitting in his seat" (for the record, it was  my seat). But all that was quickly forgotten when the boys broke out an Eyes of the World second set opener. 

I also recall Phil's kids backstage wearing mickey mouse hats and that seemed a bit cool and strange all at the same time.
